    "created_at": "2015-07-29T16:00:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-29T16:00:32Z",
    "body": "Not sure if this is related, but I've found that setting a ZoomFactor of not 1 inversely affects the height and width of the webview. For example, if my general app has a zoom factor of 2, my webview's html and body will have a width 'W' px and height 'H' px where 'W' and 'H' are half of the value of the containing element. If zoom is 1.5, 'W' and 'H' will be 2/3rds of the containing element. Weird, might be a chromium thing.\n\nI'm fairly certain this is not a CSS/HTML issue as I've explored this problem on my app for over a month at varying levels of the webview and renderer levels\n"
  },
